Dow Chemical Co said it expectsbusiness to remains strong during the fourth quarter, withseasonal increases for agricultural products, improvementanticipated for industrial specialties and continuing strengthin basic chemicals and plastics.    It said this will result in a record year for the company,noting "earnings already have exceeded the previous all-timehigh of 4.42 dlrs achieved for the full year of 1980."    For the third quarter, Dow reported earnings of 330 mlndlrs, or 1.72 dlrs a share compared to 167 mln dlrs, or 87 ctsa share a year earlier. Reuter&#3;